
Last Updated: 16-07-2025

At Asfour Delivery Logistic L.L.C, we value and respect your privacy. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal data across our system, including our two mobile applications:

Asfour Store App (used by merchants)

Asfour Staff App (used by our internal logistics and delivery staff)

By using our services, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

1. Information We Collect
From Store Users:
Business information: Store name, commercial registration, location, contact number.

Order details: Items, prices, delivery addresses, notes, and timestamps.

Device data: Device ID, app version, IP address, and logs for troubleshooting.

From Staff Users:
Personal data: Full name, mobile number, assigned routes.

Location data: Real-time GPS tracking (only during active delivery).

Performance metrics: Delivery times, completion status, and customer ratings.

2. How We Use the Information
We use the information to:

Enable order creation and delivery processing

Track order statuses and delivery performance

Communicate with stores and staff

Improve our operations and route optimization

Ensure security and compliance

Provide support and resolve technical issues

3. Location Data
For delivery staff, location tracking is used only during delivery shifts to optimize routes and confirm drop-offs. It is not tracked outside working hours.

4. Data Sharing
We do not sell or rent your data. We may share limited information with:

Payment providers (for stores using in-app payments)

Third-party logistics partners (only when assisting with deliveries)

Authorities if legally required

All third-party partners are contractually required to handle your data securely.

5. Data Security
We take strong measures to protect your data:

End-to-end encryption for order and location data

Secure server storage (DigitalOcean/Cloud provider)

Role-based access control for internal systems

6. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access your stored data

Request data correction or deletion

Withdraw consent (which may affect app functionality)

To exercise these rights, contact us at: privacy@asfour-logistics.com

7. Data Retention
We retain data only as long as necessary for:

Fulfilling our services

Meeting legal obligations

Resolving disputes or fraud investigations

8. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Our apps are not intended for use by children under 18.

9. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be notified through the apps or our website.

